0, "name": "BRN", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/BRN?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 1383357, "name": "Pattani", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Pattani?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 1416280, "name": "Wan Kadir Che Man", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Wan_Kadir_Che_Man?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 1416285, "name": "Thawee Sodsong", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Thawee_Sodsong?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 1416286, "name": "Kasturi Mahkota", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Kasturi_Mahkota?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 1750941, "name": "Muslims in South Thailand", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Muslims_in_South_Thailand?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 1884346, "name": "Southen Thailand", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Southen_Thailand?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 2210408, "name": "Southern Thailand 2012", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Southern_Thailand_2012?f_ri=204791"}]}, {"id": 39701271, "title": "1961 Anayasa Referandumu ve DP Taban\u0131", "created_at": "2019-06-26T08:23:45.952-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/39701271/1961_Anayasa_Referandumu_ve_DP_Taban%C4%B1?f_ri=204791", "dom_id": "work_39701271", "summary": "\u00d6z 27 May\u0131s 1960 askeri m\u00fcdahalesiyle y\u00f6netime el koyan Milli Birlik Komitesi, yeni bir anayasa haz\u0131rlanmas\u0131 i\u00e7in \u00fcniversiteden hukuk\u00e7ular\u0131 g\u00f6reve \u00e7a\u011f\u0131rm\u0131\u015ft\u0131. Haz\u0131rlanan yeni anayasa ile DP'nin iktidar oldu\u011fu d\u00f6nemde ya\u015fanan siyasi sorunlar, huzursuzluklar, ekonomik ve toplumsal problem-lere \u00e7\u00f6z\u00fcm bulmak istenmi\u015fti. Referandum ile halk\u0131n onay\u0131na sunulan anayasan\u0131n kabul edilmesi sivil hayata d\u00f6nmek i\u00e7in gerekli g\u00f6r\u00fclmekteydi. DP'nin siyasi hayat\u0131na son verildi\u011fi bir ortamda ba\u015flayan referandum faaliyetleri sadece anayasay\u0131 destekleyenlerin propagandalar\u0131na sahne olmu\u015f gibi g\u00f6r\u00fcnse de DP se\u00e7menine hitap etmek i\u00e7in kurulan AP de \u00f6zellikle Bat\u0131 Anadolu b\u00f6lgesinde gizli olarak anayasaya hay\u0131r oyu verilmesi \u00e7a\u011fr\u0131s\u0131nda bulunmu\u015ftu. Milli Birlik Komitesi de halkla g\u00f6r\u00fc\u015fmeler yapmak i\u00e7in kendi \u00fcyelerini Anadolu'nun \u00e7e\u015fitli \u015fehirlerine g\u00f6ndermi\u015f ve halka eski g\u00fcnlerdeki si-yasi \u00e7eki\u015fmelerinin bir daha ya\u015fanmamas\u0131 ve yeni d\u00f6nemin ihtiya\u00e7lar\u0131 i\u00e7in haz\u0131rlanan yeni anayasay\u0131 kabul etmelerini istemi\u015fti. Anayasan\u0131n getirdikleri konusunda gerek halk aras\u0131nda gerekse bas\u0131nda fazla tart\u0131\u015fma ya\u015fanmazken, anayasay\u0131 haz\u0131rlayan kurucu mecliste CHP'nin say\u0131sal \u00fcst\u00fcnl\u00fc\u011fe sahip olmas\u0131 ve CHP'li s\u00f6zc\u00fclerin anayasay\u0131 sahiplenen konu\u015fmalar yapmalar\u0131, DP taban\u0131n\u0131n k\u0131rm\u0131z\u0131 oy vermesine neden olmu\u015ftu. Gizli gizli s\u00fcrmekte olan olumsuz propagandalar ve DP'li se\u00e7menin s\u00fcre\u00e7ten d\u0131\u015flanm\u0131\u015f olmas\u0131 gibi nedenlerle referandumda elde edilen sonu\u00e7 beklenenden farkl\u0131 olmu\u015f, kat\u0131l\u0131m y\u00fcksek olmas\u0131na kar\u015f\u0131n evet oylar\u0131 y\u00fczde 70'lere bile ula\u015famam\u0131\u015ft\u0131. Olumsuz oylar\u0131n \u00e7oklu\u011fu DP taban\u0131n\u0131n askeri darbeye ve ya\u015fanan s\u00fcrece bir tepkisi idi. Elde edilen sonucu gelece\u011fe y\u00f6nelik bir iktidar \u00fcmidi olarak g\u00f6ren AP memnuniyetle kar\u015f\u0131larken, Milli Birlik Komitesi ise anayasan\u0131n kabul edilmi\u015f olmas\u0131 yeterli g\u00f6rm\u00fc\u015ft\u00fc. Devletin imk\u00e2nlar\u0131yla ve \u00fc\u00e7 partinin deste\u011fiyle y\u00fcr\u00fct\u00fclen referandum kampanyas\u0131ndan \u00e7\u0131kan sonu\u00e7 1957 se\u00e7imlerinde al\u0131nan oy haritas\u0131na benzemekte, ad\u0131 ge\u00e7en se\u00e7imde DP'yi desteklemi\u015f olan vilayetlerin anayasaya hay\u0131r oyu verdi\u011fi anla\u015f\u0131lmaktayd\u0131. Abstract On May 27, 1960, the national unity committee, which seized power under military intervention, invited universities to refer to constitutional lawyers for the preparation of a new constitution. In the prepared 1961 constitution, it was desired to find solutions to political problems and uneasiness, economic troubles and social problems in the period when the DP was in power. The adoption of the new constitution , which was presented to the public with the referendum, was deemed necessary to return civilian life. Although the referendum activities, which started in an environment where the DP's political life was terminated, seemed to be the scene of the propaganda of supporters of the constitution, the AP was set up to appeal to the DP voters, especially in the Western Anatolia region. The National Unity Committee has also sent its members to visit the country to discuss with the people and asked the public to accept the new constitution for the new period's needs and the political controversies of the old era. The fact that the", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 59872508, "asset_id": 39701271, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 21908297, "first_name": "Gazi Akademik Bak\u0131\u015f Dergisi/", "last_name": "Journal of Gazi Academic View", "domain_name": "independent", "page_name": "GaziAkademikBak\u0131\u015f", "display_name": "Gazi Akademik Bak\u0131\u015f Dergisi/  Journal of Gazi Academic View", "profile_url": "https://independent.academia.edu/GaziAkademikBak%C4%B1%C5%9F?f_ri=204791", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/21908297/6005886/19702158/s65_gazi_akademik_bak_dergisi_.journal_of_gazi_academic_view.png"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 204791, "name": "NSC", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/NSC?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 273441, "name": "AP", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/AP?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 512680, "name": "DP", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/DP?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 2620778, "name": "MGK", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/MGK?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 3296005, "name": "1960 Askeri M\u00fcdahalesi", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/1960_Askeri_M%C3%BCdahalesi?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 3296006, "name": "9 Temmuz 1961 Anayasa referandumu", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/9_Temmuz_1961_Anayasa_referandumu?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 3296007, "name": "1960 Military Intervention", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/1960_Military_Intervention?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 3296008, "name": "9 July 1961 Constitution referendum", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/9_July_1961_Constitution_referendum?f_ri=204791"}]}, {"id": 24242866, "title": "Le processus d\u00e9cisionnel en politique \u00e9trang\u00e8re des \u00c9tats-Unis lorsque le pr\u00e9sident est temporairement invalide", "created_at": "2016-04-09T16:33:20.338-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/24242866/Le_processus_d%C3%A9cisionnel_en_politique_%C3%A9trang%C3%A8re_des_%C3%89tats_Unis_lorsque_le_pr%C3%A9sident_est_temporairement_invalide?f_ri=204791", "dom_id": "work_24242866", "summary": "Ce m\u00e9moire s'int\u00e9resse au processus d\u00e9cisionnel en politique \u00e9trang\u00e8re des \u00c9tats-Unis lorsque le pr\u00e9sident s'est retrouv\u00e9 en situation d'invalidit\u00e9. Plus pr\u00e9cis\u00e9ment, cette \u00e9tude porte sur le comportement des principaux conseillers au sein du processus d\u00e9cisionnel selon la pr\u00e9sence ou l'absence du pr\u00e9sident en mettant l'accent sur les entrepreneurs politiques. L'hypoth\u00e8se d\u00e9fendue est que l'invalidit\u00e9 du pr\u00e9sident est une occasion favorisant l'\u00e9mergence d'entrepreneurs politiques qui vont tenter de saisir l'opportunit\u00e9 se pr\u00e9sentant \u00e0 eux afin de promouvoir leurs propres int\u00e9r\u00eats dans la formulation de la politique \u00e9trang\u00e8re. Pour mener \u00e0 bien cette recherche, nous analysons trois \u00e9tudes de cas qui se d\u00e9roulent dans le cadre de la guerre froide, au cours desquelles le pr\u00e9sident s'est retrouv\u00e9 en situation d'invalidit\u00e9 temporaire. Eisenhower s'est retrouv\u00e9 en situation d'invalidit\u00e9 \u00e0 trois reprises en l'espace de deux ans. Durant ces p\u00e9riodes, le processus d\u00e9cisionnel n'a pas chang\u00e9, mais le secr\u00e9taire d'\u00c9tat Dulles a pris une d\u00e9cision qui a fait d\u00e9vier la politique \u00e9trang\u00e8re en l'absence du pr\u00e9sident et dont les cons\u00e9quences internationales ont \u00e9t\u00e9 d\u00e9sastreuses. Au cours de la guerre du Kippour, Kissinger a pris en main le processus de gestion de crise et s'est appropri\u00e9 les pouvoirs pr\u00e9sidentiels de Nixon, qui \u00e9tait accabl\u00e9 par le scandale du Watergate et sans doute temporairement inapte \u00e0 gouverner \u00e0 cause de ses exc\u00e8s d'alcool. Lorsque Reagan a \u00e9t\u00e9 victime d'une tentative d'assassinat, le secr\u00e9taire d'\u00c9tat Haig tenta sans succ\u00e8s de prendre le contr\u00f4le de la gestion de crise. Cet \u00e9v\u00e8nement permit \u00e0 un groupe de conseillers de s'imposer au sein de cette administration. Toutefois, ces trois cas ont eu des r\u00e9sultats diff\u00e9rents, ce qui sugg\u00e8re que l'invalidit\u00e9 pr\u00e9sidentielle ne modifie pas syst\u00e9matiquement le processus d\u00e9cisionnel et la politique \u00e9trang\u00e8re. Enfin, cette \u00e9tude conclut que certains facteurs ont pr\u00e9d\u00e9termin\u00e9 l'impact de l'invalidit\u00e9 pr\u00e9sidentielle sur la prise de d\u00e9cision. ", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 44577480, "asset_id": 24242866, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 2842917, "first_name": "Alexandre", "last_name": "Alaoui", "domain_name": "uqam", "page_name": "AlexandreAlaoui", "display_name": "Alexandre Alaoui", "profile_url": "https://uqam.academia.edu/AlexandreAlaoui?f_ri=204791", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/2842917/933078/13746274/s65_alexandre.alaoui.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 1483, "name": "Foreign Policy Analysis", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Foreign_Policy_Analysis?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1681, "name": "Decision Making", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Decision_Making?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 31010, "name": "Presidential Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Presidential_Studies?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 36487, "name": "U.S. Foreign Policy", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/U.S._Foreign_Policy?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 85629, "name": "Richard Nixon", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Richard_Nixon?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 104491, "name": "Suez Crisis", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Suez_Crisis?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 120969, "name": "Henry A. Kissinger", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Henry_A._Kissinger?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 142422, "name": "Ronald Reagan", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Ronald_Reagan?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 204791, "name": "NSC", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/NSC?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 555330, "name": "Policy entrepreneurs", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Policy_entrepreneurs?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 959396, "name": "John Foster Dulles", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/John_Foster_Dulles?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 1035559, "name": "Yom Kippur War", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Yom_Kippur_War?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 1367722, "name": "Dwight Eisenhower", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Dwight_Eisenhower?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 2441395, "name": "Invalidit\u00e9", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Invalidit%C3%A9?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 2441396, "name": "25th Amendement", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/25th_Amendement?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 2441397, "name": "Alexander Haig", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Alexander_Haig?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 2441398, "name": "Situation Room", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Situation_Room?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 2441399, "name": "White House Staff", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/White_House_Staff?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 2441400, "name": "Presidential Incapacity", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Presidential_Incapacity?f_ri=204791"}]}, {"id": 33176281, "title": "PROFESSIONALIZING MINISTERIAL ADVISING", "created_at": "2017-05-24T06:09:21.663-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/33176281/PROFESSIONALIZING_MINISTERIAL_ADVISING?f_ri=204791", "dom_id": "work_33176281", "summary": "In this study, Professor Raymond Millen has identified a persistent challenge in U.S. efforts to provide effective security cooperation and capacity building with fragile and failing states\u2014the realm of ministerial advising. From his research and analysis, he has concluded the United States has an opportunity to close the gap between U.S. good intentions and outcomes by recommending the establishment of a professional ministerial corps.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 53260840, "asset_id": 33176281, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 24810323, "first_name": "Raymond", "last_name": "Millen", "domain_name": "pksoi", "page_name": "RaymondMillen", "display_name": "Raymond Millen", "profile_url": "https://pksoi.academia.edu/RaymondMillen?f_ri=204791", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/24810323/6711718/7581764/s65_raymond.millen.jpg_oh_2d7f6ad5df439a01fda51e4039e762cf_oe_5532c9a4___gda___1428670688_7e642fb9a5ee425ed3be87d8913e44c8"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 5523, "name": "Security Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Security_Studies?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 204791, "name": "NSC", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/NSC?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}]}, {"id": 40007715, "title": "All-trans Retinoic Acid as a Versatile Cytosolic Signal Modulator Mediated by CRABP1", "created_at": "2019-08-04T06:51:54.309-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/40007715/All_trans_Retinoic_Acid_as_a_Versatile_Cytosolic_Signal_Modulator_Mediated_by_CRABP1?f_ri=204791", "dom_id": "work_40007715", "summary": "All-trans retinoic acid (AtRA), an active metabolite of vitamin A, is recognized for its classical action as an endocrine hormone that triggers genomic effects mediated through nuclear receptors RA receptors (RARs). New evidence shows that atRA-mediated cellular responses are biphasic with rapid and delayed responses. Most of these rapid atRA responses are the outcome of its binding to cellular retinoic acid binding protein 1 (CRABP1) that is predominantly localized in cytoplasm and binds to atRA with a high affinity. This review summarizes the most recent studies of such non-genomic outcomes of atRA and the role of CRABP1 in mediating such rapid effects in different cell types. In embryonic stem cells (ESCs), atRA-CRABP1 dampens growth factor sensitivity and stemness. In a hippocampal neural stem cell (NSC) population, atRA-CRABP1 negatively modulates NSC proliferation and affects learning and memory. In cardiomyocytes, atRA-CRABP1 prevents over-activation of calcium-calmodulin-dependent protein kinase II (CaMKII), protecting heart function. These are supported by the fact that CRABP1 gene knockout (KO) mice exhibit multiple phenotypes including hippocampal NSC expansion and spontaneous cardiac hypertrophy. This indicates that more potential processes/signaling pathways involving atRA-CRABP1 may exist, which remain to be identified.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 60200507, "asset_id": 40007715, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 2935961, "first_name": "Isha", "last_name": "Nagpal", "domain_name": "bidmc", "page_name": "IshaNagpal", "display_name": "Isha Nagpal", "profile_url": "https://bidmc.academia.edu/IshaNagpal?f_ri=204791", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/2935961/970151/76764870/s65_isha.nagpal.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 146, "name": "Bioinformatics", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Bioinformatics?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 4233, "name": "Computational Biology", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Computational_Biology?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 17856, "name": "Cell Signaling", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Cell_Signaling?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 50487, "name": "Protein-Protein Interaction", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Protein-Protein_Interaction?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 52564, "name": "Vitamin A", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Vitamin_A?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 133186, "name": "Pharmacology and toxicology", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Pharmacology_and_toxicology?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 204791, "name": "NSC", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/NSC?f_ri=204791"}, {"id": 1557024, "name": "Cardiomyocyte", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Cardiomyocyte?f_ri=204791"}]}, {"id": 765737, "title": "Temporal variation of nonstructural carbohydrates in montane conifers: similarities and differences among developmental stages, species and environmental \u2026", "created_at": "2011-07-21T04:31:56.008-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/765737/Temporal_variation_of_nonstructural_carbohydrates_in_montane_conifers_similarities_and_differences_among_developmental_stages_species_and_environmental_?f_ri=204791", "dom_id": "work_765737", "summary": "Nonstructural carbohydrates (NSCs) are commonly used to assess the balance of carbon sources and sinks in plants. A notable application of this approach has been for testing hypotheses of carbon limitations of trees at their upper altitudinal limits, near the alpine. How NSCs vary in time is not well known in conifers during their critical seedling stage, despite the importance of knowing the temporal variations of NSCs in order to use snapshot measurements of NSCs to assess carbon balance. We measured NSCs in needles, separated into soluble sugars and starch, 1) over diurnal periods in seedling of Pseudotsuga menziesii (a timberline species that does not occur up to treeline), 2) throughout the growth season in seedlings of P. menziesii and Abies lasiocarpa (a species that does occur up to treeline) growing along an elevation gradient in the timberline ecotone, and furthermore 3) compared seedlings and co-occurring adults to assess variation with developmental stage. We also compared NSCs in seedlings grown under field or laboratory conditions to separate environmental from intrinsic factors affecting NSCs during early emergence. Diurnal variations in NSCs were minimal, especially compared to seasonal variation, and were detectable mainly in relatively small midday maxima of soluble sugar concentrations. Seasonal patterns of NSCs were generally (and surprisingly) similar among field and laboratory seedlings and adults. Seasonal patterns of NSCs were dominated by progressive increases in soluble sugars until winter, and by early-season peaks in starch. Nonetheless, notable differences were detectable among ages, species, and environmental conditions in 1) the timing and extent of the early-season maxima of starch and 2) the extent of the late-season maxima of soluble sugars. These differences in NSCs likely correspond with ecophysiologically relevant differences in carbon balance that could affect growth and survival of trees growing in the timberline ecotone.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 35840111, "asset_id": 765737, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 583962, "first_name": "Sheel", "last_name": "Bansal", "domain_name": "unitedstatesgeologicalsurvey", "page_name": "SheelBansal", "display_name": "Sheel Bansal", "profile_url": "https://unitedstatesgeologicalsurvey.academia.edu/SheelBansal?f_ri=204791", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/583962/1032166/13239351/s65_sheel.bansal.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 1360, "name": "Plant Ecology", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Plant_Ecology?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 58335, "name": "Plant Ecophysiology", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Plant_Ecophysiology?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 134061, "name": "Treeline", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Treeline?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 204791, "name": "NSC", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/NSC?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}]}, {"id": 32427459, "title": "Norton reviews The Field of Fight in Middle East Policy, Spring 2017", "created_at": "2017-04-14T10:21:05.130-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/32427459/Norton_reviews_The_Field_of_Fight_in_Middle_East_Policy_Spring_2017?f_ri=204791", "dom_id": "work_32427459", "summary": "Presidents typically see their national security adviser multiple times daily. Just as his predecessors did, President Donald J. Trump will count on his national security adviser to keep him abreast of hot-button issues and to present well-considered options for responding to challenges around the globe. Trump\u2019s first selection for the post was Michael T. Flynn, who lasted only 24 days before being pressured to resign. Despite Flynn\u2019s curtailed tenure, it is important to consider the ideas and policies that he has espoused because many of them are shared by other close associates of the president, and even by the president himself.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 52621927, "asset_id": 32427459, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 2217627, "first_name": "ar", "last_name": "norton", "domain_name": "bu", "page_name": "arnorton", "display_name": "ar norton", "profile_url": "https://bu.academia.edu/arnorton?f_ri=204791", "photo": "/images/s65_no_pic.png"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 18623, "name": "Middle East Politics", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Middle_East_Politics?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 36487, "name": "U.S. Foreign Policy", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/U.S._Foreign_Policy?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 204791, "name": "NSC", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/NSC?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 768791, "name": "White House", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/White_House?f_ri=204791", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1250479, "name": "Donald Trump", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Donald_Trump?f_ri=204791"}]}]